<subSubSection id="C33A651CDF7A1108FF15CF80FEB91A81" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9F3697DF7A1108FF15CF80FEB91A81" blockId="3.[151,1436,1273,2034]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">
Cespitose perennials with erect culms. Leaf sheaths sheltered by stiff, deciduous hairs, leaf blades rigid, long attenuate towards the base. Racemes mostly solitary, or eventually paired, 
<quantity id="4CD89B72DF7A1108FC7FCE59FBC91A6F" box="[1021,1136,1312,1338]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" unit="cm" value="12.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="10.0">10–15 cm</quantity>
long, with rachis broadly winged, foliaceous, partially covering the spikelets. Spikelets paired, glabrous, lower glumes 0–5-nerved, up to ½ the length of the spikelets, sometimes wanting; upper glumes obovate, 13–17-nerved, the apex truncate overtopped by the excurrent nerves; lower floret male, the lower lemma 7–9-nerved, glume-like; upper floret bisexual.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33A651CDF7A1108FF44CE99FA2518A7" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B9F3697DF7A1108FF44CE99FC4C19C3" blockId="3.[151,1436,1273,2034]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis id="B954EA85DF7A1108FF44CE99FC9C1AAF" bold="true" box="[198,805,1504,1530]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">Distribution, habitat, and conservation status:</emphasis>
―Endemic to Southern 
<collectingCountry id="F3377607DF7A1108FBDBCE98FB1D1AAE" box="[1113,1188,1505,1531]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, this relatively rare species occurs in ‘campos’ on outcropping areas in the states of 
<collectingRegion id="49E4F875DF7A1108FC03CD71FBE71977" box="[897,1118,1544,1570]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49E4F875DF7A1108FBEBCD71FAAD1977" box="[1129,1300,1544,1570]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49E4F875DF7A1108FACECD71FA251977" box="[1356,1436,1544,1570]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">Paraná</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B66DF7A1108FF1DCD57FEFF191D" author="Burman, A. G." box="[159,326,1582,1608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" pagination="101 - 116" refId="ref3666" refString="Burman, A. G. (1983) The genus Thrasyopsis Parodi (Gramineae). Phyton (Austria) 23: 101 - 116." type="journal article" year="1983">Burman 1983</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B66DF7A1108FED1CD57FDAB191D" author="Filgueiras, T. S." box="[339,530,1582,1608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" refId="ref3940" refString="Filgueiras, T. S. (2012) Thrasyopsis. In: Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro, Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / 2012 / FB 013653 (Accessed: 28 October 2012)." type="url" year="2012">Filgueiras 2012</bibRefCitation>
). The species was classified as ‘vulnerable’ (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B66DF7A1108FBA8CD57FB6D191D" author="Boldrini, I. I." box="[1066,1236,1582,1608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" pagination="63 - 77" refId="ref3536" refString="Boldrini, I. I. (2009) A flora dos Campos do Rio Grande do Sul. In: Pillar, V. P., Muller, S. C., Castilhos, Z. M. S. &amp; Jacques, A. V. A. (eds.), Campos Sulinos. Conservacao e uso sustentavel da biodiversidade. Ministerio do Meio Ambiente, Secretaria de Biodiversidade e Florestas, Departamento de Conservacao da Biodiversidade, Brasilia / DF, pp. 63 - 77." type="book chapter" year="2009">Boldrini 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and included in the list of threatened species of the Brazilian flora, because of the progressive reduction of the already small number of surviving individuals in known populations (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B66DF7A1108FCA6CD05FC5019C3" author="Valls, J. F. M. &amp; Boldrini, I. I. &amp; Longhi-Wagner, H. M. &amp; Miotto, S. T. S." box="[804,1001,1660,1686]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" pagination="139 - 154" refId="ref4813" refString="Valls, J. F. M., Boldrini, I. I., Longhi-Wagner, H. M. &amp; Miotto, S. T. S. (2009) O patrimonio floristico dos Campos: potencialidades de uso e a conservacao de seus recursos geneticos. In: Pillar, V. P., Muller, S. C., Castilhos, Z. M. S. &amp; Jacques, A. V. A. (eds.), Campos Sulinos. Conservacao e uso sustentavel da biodiversidade. Ministerio do Meio Ambiente, Secretaria de Biodiversidade e Florestas, Departamento de Conservacao da Biodiversidade, Brasilia / DF, pp. 139 - 154." type="book chapter" year="2009">
Valls 
<emphasis id="B954EA85DF7A1108FCEACD05FC1B19C0" box="[872,930,1660,1685]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
